9 Relating to campaign finance; to amend Section
10 17-5-8.1, Code of Alabama 1975; to require the redaction of
11 addresses of principal campaign committees on all campaign
12 finance filings; and to make nonsubstantive, technical
13 revisions to update the existing code language to current
14 style.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 17-5-8.1, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§17-5-8.1
19 (a) Commencing with the 2014 election cycle, all All
20 statements, reports of contributions, and expenditures, and
21 other filings required to be filed pursuant to this chapter,
22 shall be submitted electronically over the Internet by a
23 computer file containing the report information in a format
24 and medium to be prescribed by the Secretary of State.
25 (b) Commencing with the 2014 election cycle, the The
26 Secretary of State shall implement and maintain an electronic
27 database accessible by the public through the Secretary of
28 State's website which provides the capability of search and
